rows.label: qst202503_msg0001
rows.name:
92% of enemy forces neutralized.
It is judged that the remainder are
incapable of continuing combat.

rows.label: qst202503_msg0003
rows.name:
A scan of the surroundings shows
no new enemy appearances.

rows.label: qst202503_msg0004
rows.name:
A-Amazing, mo...[ML:Dash ] You really
defeated them all, mo.

rows.label: qst202503_msg0005
rows.name:
Well, KOS-MOS Re: pretty much
blew them all away, though.

rows.label: qst202503_msg0007
rows.name:
I believe I chose the optimal
action from the available options
in the current situation.

rows.label: qst202503_msg0010
rows.name:
Yeah. We were saved
thanks to KOS-MOS Re:.

rows.label: qst202503_msg0012
rows.name:
However, that attack of KOS-MOS
Re:'s was likely observed in
neighboring countries.

rows.label: qst202503_msg0013
rows.name:
True, that light was probably
visible from Luxuria and Superbia.

rows.label: qst202503_msg0014
rows.name:
If we're not careful, this could
turn into a huge incident.

rows.label: qst202503_msg0015
rows.name:
We also need to warn people
about these artificial Blades.

rows.label: qst202503_msg0016
rows.name:
We should probably report
this to King Serich first.

rows.label: qst202503_msg0017
rows.name:
You're right. If we don't report
it soon, he'll start to worry.

rows.label: qst202503_msg0018
rows.name:
He's a worrier, after all.
Let's hurry to Theoscaldia,
the royal palace of Luxuria.
